The Daily Show 2014 05 01 David Spade WEB-DL

David Spade is a stand-up comedian and actor whose first hour-long special in more than ten years, "David Spade: My Fake Problems," airs on Comedy Central on Sunday, May 4 at 10 p.m. In 1990, Spade became a writer and cast member on "Saturday Night Live." Throughout the 1990s, he appeared in movies such as "Black Sheep" (1996) and "Tommy Boy" (1995), which both co-starred Chris Farley. His other credits include "Grown Ups 2" (2013), "Grown Ups" (2010), "Grandma's Boy" (2006) and "Joe Dirt" (2001). Spade also starred in the sitcoms "Rules of Engagement," "Just Shoot Me!" and "8 Simple Rules."
